<h3><strong><strong>Finished Pathway? Continue Your Education.</strong></strong></h3>
<p>Following the completion of Pathway, students may apply to become official degree-seeking students at BYU-Idaho. Students can choose to enter BYU-Idaho's Online Degree program (which locks in Pathway's <a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/pathway/tuition" target="_blank">reduced tuition rate</a>), or may apply to study on campus in Rexburg.</p>
<p>Students who enter the Online Degree program have over 15 options to choose from as they begin working toward a professional certificate, an associate degree, and/or a bachelor's degree. Learn more about BYU-Idaho's <a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/online-degrees-and-certificates" target="_blank">online degree options</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Steps to Advancement</h2>
<ol>
<li>Successfully complete Pathway with at least a "B" average (3.0 (<a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/online-support-center/faq#IDx28032" target="_blank">GPA calculator</a>). (Only BYU-Idaho courses count toward the GPA; institute courses do not.)</li>
<li>Browse available&nbsp;<a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/online-degrees-and-certificates" target="_blank">Online Degrees</a>. Find which one is right for you.</li>
<li>Work with your academic advisor to solidify your graduation plan.</li>
<li>Apply as a degree-seeking student.<ol>
<li>Agree to live by the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/StudentHonor/UniversityStandards.htm" target="_blank">honor code</a>.</li>
<li>Get an ecclesiastical endorsement from your bishop and stake president.</li>
<li>Complete an application (steps outlined below).</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<h3><strong>Application Process</strong></h3>
<ol>
<li>Visit&nbsp;<a href="http://besmart.com/" target="_blank">Besmart.com</a>&nbsp;to complete your application.</li>
</ol>
